In No Context, you'll be making connections using random art from the fabulous webcomic creator Mr. Lovenstein!&nbsp;

At the start of the game, each player will be assigned one of up to 7 target images that they are trying to get everyone else to guess to secure some sweet, SWEET points! These images are selected from some of the most unforgettable panels of Mr. Lovenstein's catalog.&nbsp;

On their turn, players will select another panel from those available in the comparison row and place it in one of their section of the board's spaces.&nbsp; They will place the card with the green check mark side face up to indicate their target image is like this card in some way, or with the red x side up saying that their target image is unlike this card in some way. Each player will be able to do this process 3 times to give some guidance to the other players for guessing.

However, at any point if a player feels confident they know what target image card belongs to another player, they may place their corresponding numbered bet card face down in that players bet spot. Players only have one copy for each space so make sure to bide your time or know the risks if you go sooner.&nbsp;

Once all bets are in, players will take turns revealing the&nbsp; guesses made about their card and what card was actually theirs. Correct bets get points in the order they were placed so those who wait too long may miss out on points even if they were correct. Be ready to explain yourself after the round is done as hearing the thoughts behind why your friends made the connections they did is the funniest part of the game!

-description from developer

Take on the role of an elemental sovereign, shaping the very nature of reality in this fast-moving board game!

2 to 4 players take turns to draft and play colorful (and colorblind-friendly) hexagonal tiles to match specific patterns and meet their own secret objective. With several dozen pattern cards, variable objectives, and a game state that's constantly in flux, you'll never play the same way twice. Simple setup, easy-to-learn rules, and a short play time of around 30 minutes means there's always time for one more game&hellip;

&mdash;description from the publisher

You finally get to the transfer room, answering the urging call of Laura. The AI is awaiting, impatient. &laquo;I assume it is impossible for you to arrive on time, so I will get straight to the point. Meet Bob immediately, there is no time to lose.&raquo;

Bob greets you with his usual countenance, standing in front of the pods. &laquo;As Laura stated, there&rsquo;s no time to lose!

You know that we don&rsquo;t know much about Mallartia. It&rsquo;s the only country that aligned against the creation of the T.I.M.E Agency, so they have blocked all communication efforts since the very beginning.

We&rsquo;ve got serious suspicions that they are trying to develop their own Tachyon Insertion technology, and you can bet that would be no good for all mankind.

Now we have an opportunity to, well... fix the situation. We have received a transmission from one of our inserted confidents telling us that he located some vital information for the rising of their leader Daerek Mallart. You will go to a military bunker, and the year is 2027, just before the Mallartian regime rose from the ashes of the war.&raquo;

&mdash;description from the designer

粉碎计划：东山岛1953 ("Plan Shatter: Dongshan Island，1953") is a two player wargame with the theme of the landing operation of the National Revolutionary Army(NRA) on Dongshan Island(东山岛) on July 16, 1953. One player plays the role of the People's Liberation Army(PLA), and the other plays the role of the NRA.

This is a special battle, and when the NRA landed, there was a huge disparity in strength between the two sides. NRA had an absolute advantage of about 10-1, not only in terms of sea and air superiority, but also in the presence of the first deployed special force&mdash;the paratrooper battalion. Hu Lian(胡琏) thought he had a safe chance of winning and could quickly occupy the entire island, and then use the dangerous terrain to implement defense, in order to demonstrate the strength of NRA to the United States and lay the groundwork for future counterattacks on the mainland. As a result, PLA on the island stubbornly resisted and held onto the crucial Eight Foot Gate(八尺门) Ferry. The reinforcements rushed from the mainland and entered the battlefield half a day later. At this point, the crucial role of the commander was demonstrated, and Hu Lian decided to immediately retreat. While feinting on the front line, the rear troops retreated in an orderly manner. In just one day, the already deployed troops were gathered and boarded, completing a more difficult retreat than an attack. The successful recapture of Dongshan Island by PLA has shed its former shame.

The mechanism of this game was modified based on Kinmen 1949: The Battle that Saved Taiwan.

Scale = 800 meters /hex;

     time = 8 hours /GT;
     size = battalion or company / unit.

La Bataille de Mont Saint Jean came in 2 editions, an Expansion Kit edition and a Deluxe edition. This entry is for the Expansion Kit edition.

For the expansion kit you must own La Bataille de Ligny and La Bataille des Quatre Bras as it only contains four 34 x 22" maps, special rules and background. (The Deluxe Edition contains those items plus the counters and basic rules.)

Mont St. Jean is the French name for the Battle of Waterloo, and the Prussians called this The battle of Belle Alliance.

scale = 100 m/hex; 
time = 20 min/GT; 
strength = 50-100 men/SP (Regimental/Brigade Size)

Something sinister lurks in the shadows, a looming threat only a few are even aware of. A diabolical plot slowly takes form, its goal something you can only guess at, but one thing is for certain: at the center of it all is a young, headstrong mutant, Hope Summers. For some reason, the villains&rsquo; plans hinge on Hope, and she may be in over her head&hellip;

X-Force has arrived in Marvel Champions: The Card Game! As the game&rsquo;s sixth campaign expansion, NeXt Evolution adds a pile of classic X-Force characters to the scene, including two new playable heroes, Cable and Domino, each of whom comes with a pre-built deck ready to play from the get-go. Face off against notorious villains, such as the Marauders, Juggernaut, and Mister Sinister, and work together to overcome a fresh batch of challenges. This expansion includes five brand-new scenarios, each of which can be played individually or as part of a larger campaign.

&mdash;description from the publisher

